00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:42,272 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:46,693 --> 00:00:49,655
I look forward to working with you,
Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

3
00:01:00,916 --> 00:01:03,460
Deal sealed.

4
00:01:07,589 --> 00:01:08,924
Damn it.

5
00:01:12,344 --> 00:01:13,637
Sir.

6
00:01:17,182 --> 00:01:20,018
What in the world is going on?

7
00:01:20,102 --> 00:01:23,105
It means I'm buying your company
with my pocket money.

8
00:01:23,188 --> 00:01:24,815
Mr. Son, perfect timing.

9
00:01:24,898 --> 00:01:26,316
You'll need to clean this up.

10
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:29,277
I just made them an offer
they can't refuse.

11
00:01:30,362 --> 00:01:32,531
-Sir, not again…
-Yes, that's right.

12
00:01:33,198 --> 00:01:36,159
It's exactly what you're thinking.

13
00:01:37,953 --> 00:01:39,830
Mr. Son, you take care of them.

14
00:01:41,915 --> 00:01:43,208
Please follow me.

15
00:01:44,543 --> 00:01:46,086
Ms. Shin, you come this way.

16
00:01:48,588 --> 00:01:49,923
Which way?

17
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:53,760
Here.

18
00:01:54,761 --> 00:01:55,804
Towards me.

19
00:02:03,979 --> 00:02:06,189
Why does he keep smiling?

20
00:02:07,107 --> 00:02:08,775
A man should not be so frivolous.

21
00:02:21,705 --> 00:02:24,416
EPISODE 4
BEYOND UNDERSTANDING

22
00:02:38,555 --> 00:02:40,390
I can't stand looking at your red face.

23
00:02:40,474 --> 00:02:41,975
Do something about it.

24
00:02:43,185 --> 00:02:45,896
What? No.
I didn't mean for you to drink it.

25
00:02:48,148 --> 00:02:49,900
Cha Se-gye, speak plainly.

26
00:02:49,983 --> 00:02:50,942
What are you scheming?

27
00:02:51,026 --> 00:02:52,944
What now? What's your problem?

28
00:02:53,028 --> 00:02:54,070
Given the situation,

29
00:02:54,154 --> 00:02:57,240
this contract business seems to be
anything but simple.

30
00:02:57,324 --> 00:02:58,450
I am no fool.

31
00:02:59,034 --> 00:03:00,702
You have sense, but no shame.

32
00:03:00,786 --> 00:03:02,954
If anything, you should be
on your knees thanking me.

33
00:03:03,038 --> 00:03:05,457
You can't afford
to be talking to me like this.

34
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:07,626
Bow down to you? What utter nonsense.

35
00:03:07,709 --> 00:03:11,546
I have never bowed down
to anyone in my entire life.

36
00:03:13,423 --> 00:03:17,010
No wonder you're still an unknown actress.

37
00:03:17,093 --> 00:03:19,429
I'm only saying this once, so listen up.

38
00:03:19,513 --> 00:03:21,139
The first law of investment.

39
00:03:21,223 --> 00:03:23,683
Buy on fear, sell on hype.

40
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:26,394
I'm buying you at the lower limit,
just before delisting,

41
00:03:26,478 --> 00:03:28,855
so I can sell you off at the peak.

42
00:03:28,939 --> 00:03:31,066
Sell me? Are you saying
you're going to traffic me?

43
00:03:31,149 --> 00:03:33,777
Not trafficking. Investing.

44
00:03:34,444 --> 00:03:35,904
Investing, you say?

45
00:03:38,657 --> 00:03:41,993
In other words,
you intend to bet big on my potential.

46
00:03:42,536 --> 00:03:43,745
Is that what you mean?

47
00:03:43,829 --> 00:03:45,247
More or less.

48
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:46,998
You could have just said that.

49
00:03:47,082 --> 00:03:48,083
Why talk in circles?

50
00:03:52,128 --> 00:03:54,756
Now I finally see why you possess
such an obstinate spirit.

51
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:58,510
You have blocked out the sun.
No wonder you are bitter and twisted.

52
00:04:00,804 --> 00:04:04,266
Just look at that wide open view.
Is it not the most refreshing?

53
00:04:04,349 --> 00:04:06,309
What are you doing? Someone might see.

54
00:04:20,448 --> 00:04:22,409
"Vast heavens, precious earth."

55
00:04:22,492 --> 00:04:25,579
Your spirit grows cold
because you turn from such precious light.

56
00:04:25,662 --> 00:04:28,206
Some of us have no windows
and stare at walls all day.

57
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:29,583
You take it for granted.

58
00:04:30,542 --> 00:04:31,960
You have no windows at home?

59
00:04:33,503 --> 00:04:36,631
I do, but it is a window
in name only. That is the issue.

60
00:04:38,508 --> 00:04:40,927
Enough about the windows.
We're done here.

61
00:04:41,011 --> 00:04:42,679
Shouldn't you be going now?

62
00:04:42,762 --> 00:04:44,139
I was just leaving.

63
00:04:45,891 --> 00:04:46,766
Unbelievable.

64
00:04:55,108 --> 00:04:57,736
That man blows hot and cold.

65
00:04:58,445 --> 00:04:59,905
I mean, he beckons me to follow,

66
00:04:59,988 --> 00:05:02,824
and then he casts me aside
the moment he is done with me.

67
00:05:10,206 --> 00:05:11,207
Oh no.

68
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:13,752
When did this get so swollen?

69
00:05:19,507 --> 00:05:22,302
I can't stand that bright red face.
Do something about it.

70
00:05:29,517 --> 00:05:31,603
He did not give it to me to drink.

71
00:05:31,686 --> 00:05:33,563
He gave it to me to rub on my face.

72
00:05:35,774 --> 00:05:38,985
That Cha Se-gye. He is so uselessly soft.

73
00:05:44,324 --> 00:05:45,450
Why did I do that?

74
00:05:46,076 --> 00:05:48,578
Why did I make
such a reckless, unplanned move?

75
00:05:48,662 --> 00:05:51,456
Did that weird dream break my brain?

76
00:05:51,539 --> 00:05:54,501
<i>Then again, a meticulous planner like you</i>
<i>would never go off track.</i>

77
00:05:54,584 --> 00:05:57,837
That is, unless you've fallen in love.

78
00:05:57,921 --> 00:05:59,547
Me? With a crazy woman like that?

79
00:05:59,631 --> 00:06:01,508
Not unless I'm dead and buried
in the dirt.

80
00:06:01,591 --> 00:06:03,760
-Did some dirt get in your eye?
-Damn it.

81
00:06:03,843 --> 00:06:05,387
Shall I get you some eye drops?

82
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:07,180
What? When did you get here?

83
00:06:07,263 --> 00:06:09,432
I've been here since Ms. Shin left.

84
00:06:09,516 --> 00:06:12,394
Are you a hitman or something?
I can't even hear you breathe.

85
00:06:12,477 --> 00:06:14,396
You said my breathing bothered you,

86
00:06:14,479 --> 00:06:16,481
so I honed this skill.
Zero-gravity breathing.

87
00:06:21,611 --> 00:06:22,737
So?

88
00:06:24,489 --> 00:06:25,365
What did you hear?

89
00:06:25,448 --> 00:06:26,574
"Is my brain broken?"

90
00:06:26,658 --> 00:06:28,553
"With a crazy woman like that?"

91
00:06:28,609 --> 00:06:30,078
"Maybe when I'm dead…"

92
00:06:30,161 --> 00:06:31,496
That's enough.

93
00:06:31,571 --> 00:06:33,957
I think this situation could be
quite easily misconstrued.

94
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,792
You have to read between the lines.

95
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:37,627
I don't let things

96
00:06:37,711 --> 00:06:40,088
like compassion or pity sway me.

97
00:06:40,171 --> 00:06:42,215
I am no humanist
when it comes to business.

98
00:06:42,298 --> 00:06:44,926
Yes, I'm already aware of that.

99
00:06:45,010 --> 00:06:46,636
After that rear-end collision last year,

100
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,180
you had me working all night
with casts on both legs.

101
00:06:49,264 --> 00:06:50,140
Wow.

102
00:06:50,223 --> 00:06:52,559
No one with a shred
of humanity could do that.

103
00:06:52,642 --> 00:06:54,936
-I understood then.
-Okay, you can leave now.

104
00:07:09,659 --> 00:07:11,494
Just a few slaps to the face,

105
00:07:12,037 --> 00:07:14,789
and I'm acting like some forlorn stray
caught in the rain.

106
00:07:15,707 --> 00:07:16,875
What a fool.

107
00:07:22,422 --> 00:07:23,423
Go away.

108
00:07:23,506 --> 00:07:24,424
Shoo.

109
00:07:28,136 --> 00:07:29,220
Shoo. Go.

110
00:07:30,346 --> 00:07:31,306
Go to your owner.

111
00:07:31,848 --> 00:07:32,932
Shoo.

112
00:07:33,516 --> 00:07:35,852
By the looks of you, you must be homeless.

113
00:07:36,853 --> 00:07:38,021
So am I.

114
00:07:38,605 --> 00:07:40,190
Clinging to me is pointless.

115
00:07:48,907 --> 00:07:49,783
Hey, dog.

116
00:07:50,533 --> 00:07:51,493
Stop following me.

117
00:07:53,328 --> 00:07:54,579
You are not wanted here.

118
00:07:58,041 --> 00:07:58,958
Jeez.

119
00:08:04,255 --> 00:08:05,298
Go away!

120
00:08:08,009 --> 00:08:09,803
No, I did not ask you to fetch.

121
00:08:15,475 --> 00:08:17,352
Why are you so clingy?

122
00:08:18,394 --> 00:08:19,729
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

123
00:08:19,813 --> 00:08:21,815
<i>Windfall luck was never in my fate.</i>

124
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:27,237
<i>I may possess exceptional talents</i>
<i>and striking looks,</i>

125
00:08:27,737 --> 00:08:30,240
<i>but the winds have been too favorable.</i>

126
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:33,827
Yes, windfalls that blow in without effort

127
00:08:33,910 --> 00:08:35,662
are bound to blow back.

128
00:08:35,745 --> 00:08:37,580
He may call it an "investment,"

129
00:08:37,664 --> 00:08:40,750
but that obstinate man
must still want something from me.

130
00:08:40,834 --> 00:08:42,585
Why else would he be such a sucker?

131
00:08:45,797 --> 00:08:48,591
Jeez, you're always watching dramas.

132
00:08:48,675 --> 00:08:51,219
If you put that drive to good use,
you'd already be employed.

133
00:08:51,302 --> 00:08:53,805
Why are you nagging me?
Even my mom doesn't do that.

134
00:08:53,888 --> 00:08:55,640
Even job seekers need room to breathe.

135
00:08:55,723 --> 00:08:59,102
I have never once seen you studying.

136
00:08:59,185 --> 00:09:01,771
Are you a fan of Yoon Ji-hyo or something?

137
00:09:02,313 --> 00:09:03,773
<i>Are you a Yoon Ji-hyo fan too?</i>

138
00:09:03,857 --> 00:09:04,983
A fan?

139
00:09:05,066 --> 00:09:06,985
Silently rooting for them makes you a fan.

140
00:09:07,068 --> 00:09:09,946
You wish them well, worry about them,
and send them gifts.

141
00:09:11,906 --> 00:09:14,492
<i>Of course. He must be my fan.</i>

142
00:09:15,285 --> 00:09:17,078
<i>So the beef was a tribute offering.</i>

143
00:09:18,246 --> 00:09:19,789
My good man.

144
00:09:19,873 --> 00:09:21,791
Are these so-called fans

145
00:09:21,875 --> 00:09:23,668
like guardian angels?

146
00:09:23,751 --> 00:09:25,670
Always worrying about useless things,

147
00:09:25,753 --> 00:09:28,298
wishing you well, and taking your side?

148
00:09:28,923 --> 00:09:30,091
Guardian angels?

149
00:09:30,175 --> 00:09:32,260
Well, that's basically what it means.

150
00:09:32,343 --> 00:09:35,430
Then what should I do for this fan?

151
00:09:35,513 --> 00:09:38,641
Why do anything?
Your existence alone is a gift to them.

152
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:41,853
They offer such kindness
and expect nothing in return?

153
00:09:41,936 --> 00:09:44,522
No, that's not it. These days,

154
00:09:44,606 --> 00:09:46,482
stars give back to their fans.

155
00:09:46,566 --> 00:09:48,318
They call it a "gift in return."

156
00:09:48,401 --> 00:09:49,611
-Gift…
-A gift in return.

157
00:09:49,694 --> 00:09:50,695
A gift in return.

158
00:09:50,778 --> 00:09:52,697
Then again, even our Lady Ji-hyo

159
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:54,407
buys her fans luxury goods

160
00:09:54,490 --> 00:09:56,159
and writes them letters by hand.

161
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,203
Luxury goods?

162
00:09:58,995 --> 00:10:00,205
Handwritten letters…

163
00:10:01,247 --> 00:10:04,626
So this… "gift in return" business.

164
00:10:04,709 --> 00:10:06,461
What else does it entail?

165
00:10:06,544 --> 00:10:09,130
Using the launch of Dynaestie
as a stepping stone,

166
00:10:09,214 --> 00:10:11,799
Biojei has decided to acquire
Shin Seo-ri's talent agency.

167
00:10:11,883 --> 00:10:14,427
An anonymous company poll
on Ms. Shin Seo-ri's public image

168
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:16,554
showed a positive response.

169
00:10:16,638 --> 00:10:18,681
So there were no major objections,

170
00:10:18,765 --> 00:10:20,099
but the funding is a concern.

171
00:10:20,725 --> 00:10:23,144
The Kaiserman issue
also remains unresolved.

172
00:10:23,228 --> 00:10:26,481
Don't worry about that.
I'll find a way to handle it.

173
00:10:31,986 --> 00:10:34,405
What are you doing here?
You never come to my fishing spot.

174
00:10:34,489 --> 00:10:37,200
That's a bit harsh to say
to your only grandson.

175
00:10:37,283 --> 00:10:39,577
Coming here on your own, unannounced,

176
00:10:39,661 --> 00:10:42,121
must mean you come
with ulterior motives. Am I wrong?

177
00:10:42,205 --> 00:10:43,998
Okay, I'll be frank, Grandfather.

178
00:10:44,082 --> 00:10:46,167
I need a loan against my trust fund.

179
00:10:46,876 --> 00:10:50,880
You ask for money so easily,
as if you're owed it?

180
00:10:50,964 --> 00:10:52,173
You think money is easy?

181
00:10:52,257 --> 00:10:54,717
If it were that easy,
I wouldn't look so defeated.

182
00:10:55,218 --> 00:10:56,803
I've given this a lot of thought.

183
00:10:56,886 --> 00:10:58,554
Yes, Attorney Choi told me

184
00:10:58,638 --> 00:11:01,224
you borrowed investment money
from Mun-do.

185
00:11:01,307 --> 00:11:04,269
You need quick cash
if you're starting a new business.

186
00:11:05,395 --> 00:11:08,314
When it comes to backing,
nothing beats the Bank of Grandpa.

187
00:11:08,398 --> 00:11:09,732
It won't be free money, punk.

188
00:11:09,816 --> 00:11:12,986
Did you ever see me make
a losing deal, even with family?

189
00:11:13,069 --> 00:11:14,696
What do you want this time?

190
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:17,615
Let's go. I'll buy you a nice dinner.

191
00:11:17,699 --> 00:11:20,076
You think you can
just buy me off with a meal?

192
00:11:20,159 --> 00:11:21,244
Forget it.

193
00:11:21,327 --> 00:11:22,704
I have somewhere else to be.

194
00:11:22,787 --> 00:11:24,865
JINMI JANGSUGOL PORK BACKBONE STEW

195
00:11:24,964 --> 00:11:26,333
Gosh, this place is packed today.

196
00:11:26,408 --> 00:11:27,983
It's full, Chairman Cha. Wait out there.

197
00:11:28,094 --> 00:11:29,752
No perks for a 40-year regular?

198
00:11:29,836 --> 00:11:32,547
I've been buying your soup
since your shantytown days.

199
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:34,757
It doesn't matter
if you're a 40-year regular or a CEO.

200
00:11:34,841 --> 00:11:36,092
Here, there's one rule.

201
00:11:36,175 --> 00:11:38,303
Everyone waits in the same line.
Now get out.

202
00:11:38,386 --> 00:11:40,013
You're one stubborn old lady.

203
00:11:40,096 --> 00:11:42,265
It's just that I don't have time today.

204
00:11:42,348 --> 00:11:43,683
My goodness.

205
00:11:44,809 --> 00:11:47,312
Hey, what about sharing
a table with someone?

206
00:11:47,395 --> 00:11:48,938
That young lady is by herself.

207
00:11:51,774 --> 00:11:55,069
As if kids these days
share tables with old geezers!

208
00:11:56,696 --> 00:11:57,989
Hold on.

209
00:11:59,115 --> 00:12:02,035
Excuse me, miss.
There aren't any seats left, you see.

210
00:12:02,118 --> 00:12:03,745
Could I possibly join you?

211
00:12:03,828 --> 00:12:05,747
I'm almost done. Please wait.

212
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:09,334
I'm just a little short on time, you see.
Just help me out here.

213
00:12:09,417 --> 00:12:11,336
Then you should have timed it better.

214
00:12:11,419 --> 00:12:14,047
-Good grief. I do not owe you a seat.
-Well, then…

215
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:17,216
I'll pay for your meal, miss.

216
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:18,301
How about it?

217
00:12:24,932 --> 00:12:26,601
Deal sealed.

218
00:12:41,407 --> 00:12:43,951
<i>That wide open view.</i>
<i>Is it not the most refreshing?</i>

219
00:12:44,035 --> 00:12:46,579
Some of us have no windows
and stare at walls all day.

220
00:12:46,662 --> 00:12:47,872
You take it for granted.

221
00:12:49,457 --> 00:12:52,377
Mr. Son, are there still apartments
without windows these days?

222
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:53,920
I mean, don't you need windows

223
00:12:54,003 --> 00:12:55,588
to get a building permit?

224
00:12:55,671 --> 00:12:56,964
It could be built illegally.

225
00:12:57,048 --> 00:12:59,092
Cheap rentals and boarding houses
might not have them.

226
00:12:59,175 --> 00:13:00,468
Really? No windows?

227
00:13:00,551 --> 00:13:03,388
So, a window that opens
to face a wall is also possible?

228
00:13:03,971 --> 00:13:05,264
Usually, in a boarding house,

229
00:13:05,348 --> 00:13:07,308
windows, bathrooms, and refrigerators

230
00:13:07,392 --> 00:13:09,268
are all considered amenities.

231
00:13:09,352 --> 00:13:11,604
I guess the cheapest rooms
wouldn't have them.

232
00:13:12,897 --> 00:13:14,649
Why the sudden interest?

233
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,736
Oh, I was just passing by a TV
playing <i>Screening Humanity.</i>

234
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:19,946
I see…

235
00:13:27,662 --> 00:13:31,040
Why is a young person like you
eating soup all by yourself?

236
00:13:31,124 --> 00:13:32,500
I prefer being alone.

237
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:34,669
Nothing to grate on my nerves either.

238
00:13:35,086 --> 00:13:36,045
That's true.

239
00:13:42,301 --> 00:13:43,386
<i>Hold on.</i>

240
00:13:45,555 --> 00:13:47,223
<i>Judging by his facial features,</i>

241
00:13:47,306 --> 00:13:50,601
<i>his disposition is petty</i>
<i>and insufferably thin-skinned,</i>

242
00:13:51,227 --> 00:13:53,396
<i>but he has a "hanging gallbladder" nose.</i>

243
00:13:53,479 --> 00:13:55,273
<i>His coffers are generously lined.</i>

244
00:13:55,898 --> 00:13:57,733
<i>He is blessed with wealth</i>
<i>and ample provisions.</i>

245
00:13:57,817 --> 00:13:59,777
<i>The classic face of a man</i>
<i>of immense means.</i>

246
00:13:59,861 --> 00:14:00,987
<i>In that case…</i>

247
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:02,155
Excuse me, mistress!

248
00:14:02,238 --> 00:14:04,532
-One seafood pancake, please.
-Right away.

249
00:14:05,032 --> 00:14:07,368
Miss, why did you order that?

250
00:14:07,452 --> 00:14:10,288
I was just thinking,
and I realized suppertime is upon us.

251
00:14:10,913 --> 00:14:13,374
Peak evening hours,
when establishments are at their busiest.

252
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:16,461
You are bound to wait anywhere you go,
yet you secured this table with ease.

253
00:14:16,544 --> 00:14:18,921
So adding a pancake should make it even.

254
00:14:19,464 --> 00:14:20,840
Do you not agree?

255
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:25,845
It does feel like I'm fleeced
with my eyes wide open,

256
00:14:25,928 --> 00:14:28,806
-but sure. Why not?
-Do not worry. I will share half.

257
00:14:29,474 --> 00:14:30,892
Oh, right.

258
00:14:30,975 --> 00:14:33,478
-One more thing, while we are at it.
-What now?

259
00:14:37,523 --> 00:14:40,318
What are you going to do
with these leftover bones?

260
00:14:40,401 --> 00:14:42,445
I have an important use for them.

261
00:14:43,988 --> 00:14:45,865
You know, I'm known for being frugal,

262
00:14:45,948 --> 00:14:48,576
but you're really something else, miss.

263
00:14:48,659 --> 00:14:50,495
You'll never starve, that's for sure.

264
00:14:50,578 --> 00:14:52,455
I get that a lot.

265
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,832
Thanks to you, I ate very well.

266
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:56,709
Take care.

267
00:14:59,086 --> 00:15:00,838
A free meal and free bones.

268
00:15:00,922 --> 00:15:03,216
She really got her money's worth.

269
00:15:10,890 --> 00:15:13,518
Hey! Come here, Doggy! Spot! Scruffy!

270
00:15:13,601 --> 00:15:15,269
Rover! Rusty!

271
00:15:19,065 --> 00:15:22,527
Where could that dog have gone?
Did it just vanish into thin air?

272
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:24,195
Did someone already take it?

273
00:15:24,278 --> 00:15:27,782
Whatever.
Who cares if someone took it or not?

274
00:15:27,865 --> 00:15:29,951
My own belly is a prisoner of starvation.

275
00:16:03,776 --> 00:16:04,694
What?

276
00:16:07,321 --> 00:16:08,322
It was you?

277
00:16:08,906 --> 00:16:11,242
Dingy little dog. Go on, get away.

278
00:16:11,325 --> 00:16:12,994
I guess that is a dog's nose for you.

279
00:16:13,077 --> 00:16:14,453
How did you ever find me?

280
00:16:20,585 --> 00:16:23,170
I did not throw this for you to fetch.

281
00:16:23,254 --> 00:16:24,922
I threw it to make you go away.

282
00:16:25,423 --> 00:16:26,841
Silly dog.

283
00:16:31,304 --> 00:16:34,056
Hey, spit that out!
You should not eat things like that.

284
00:16:34,599 --> 00:16:36,934
Are you hungry?

285
00:16:37,435 --> 00:16:38,352
Damn it.

286
00:16:38,436 --> 00:16:40,688
Damn stray dogs and cats.

287
00:16:40,771 --> 00:16:42,773
If I ever catch you, you'll be toast!

288
00:16:42,857 --> 00:16:44,483
-You wait here.
-Just look at this mess!

289
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,110
-I will get you some food.
-Unbelievable.

290
00:16:46,193 --> 00:16:47,320
Damn it.

291
00:16:47,987 --> 00:16:49,196
Damn it all.

292
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:51,032
I hate my life.

293
00:16:51,115 --> 00:16:52,158
Jeez.

294
00:16:53,159 --> 00:16:54,535
Seriously?

295
00:16:54,619 --> 00:16:56,203
I can't believe this.

296
00:16:56,287 --> 00:16:58,873
Hey, Unit 203!
Where have you been all day?

297
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:01,917
I was just coming back from a stroll.

298
00:17:02,001 --> 00:17:02,918
What is it?

299
00:17:03,002 --> 00:17:06,464
You put our boarding house's number
on your résumé, didn't you?

300
00:17:06,547 --> 00:17:08,633
The police just called.
It was absolute chaos.

301
00:17:08,716 --> 00:17:10,009
The police station?

302
00:17:10,968 --> 00:17:12,386
The police station?

303
00:17:13,346 --> 00:17:14,388
The police? Why?

304
00:17:14,472 --> 00:17:16,807
<i>The assistant director</i>
<i>from that home shopping channel</i>

305
00:17:16,891 --> 00:17:18,434
<i>filed an assault complaint.</i>

306
00:17:18,517 --> 00:17:21,145
<i>I'm calling you after handing it over</i>
<i>to the legal team.</i>

307
00:17:21,228 --> 00:17:22,146
Really?

308
00:17:22,688 --> 00:17:24,398
I'm sure you handled it.

309
00:17:24,482 --> 00:17:27,943
I assume he got a bogus doctor's note
to try and get a big payout.

310
00:17:28,027 --> 00:17:29,612
I'd rather do without cheap rumors.

311
00:17:29,695 --> 00:17:31,864
Pay him double what he wants
and just shut him up.

312
00:17:31,947 --> 00:17:34,492
<i>Yes, sir. As a precaution,</i>
<i>I'll ensure Ms. Shin's case</i>

313
00:17:34,575 --> 00:17:35,910
<i>is separated.</i>

314
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:37,370
Shin Seo-ri?

315
00:17:39,747 --> 00:17:40,915
What about her?

316
00:17:42,124 --> 00:17:44,460
<i>Okay. Everyone needs to calm down.</i>

317
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,420
So, let me get this straight.

318
00:17:46,504 --> 00:17:48,923
You grabbed him, and his arm was injured.

319
00:17:49,006 --> 00:17:52,093
And he refused to pay you your wages.

320
00:17:52,176 --> 00:17:54,220
So, we have unpaid wages and assault.

321
00:17:54,303 --> 00:17:56,222
Are you going to sue each other now?

322
00:17:56,305 --> 00:17:57,264
What do you mean?

323
00:17:57,348 --> 00:18:00,059
Her wages have nothing to do with me.
Just the assault.

324
00:18:00,559 --> 00:18:03,187
All this fuss over a simple wrist grab?

325
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:06,565
If I had tripped you,
you would probably pretend to be dying.

326
00:18:06,649 --> 00:18:08,651
You are even making this dog laugh.

327
00:18:09,610 --> 00:18:12,571
What? Because of you,
I'm about to lose my job.

328
00:18:12,655 --> 00:18:13,614
My medical bills

329
00:18:13,698 --> 00:18:15,866
and emotional distress.
You'll pay for it all!

330
00:18:15,950 --> 00:18:17,910
I thought the compensation was settled.

331
00:18:19,995 --> 00:18:21,497
Double the standard settlement

332
00:18:22,039 --> 00:18:23,541
for a six-week injury diagnosis,

333
00:18:23,624 --> 00:18:25,251
generously provided by my legal team.

334
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:27,002
Was that not enough?

335
00:18:27,086 --> 00:18:28,671
-Who are you?
-Oh, right.

336
00:18:32,383 --> 00:18:34,093
Along with this woman,

337
00:18:34,176 --> 00:18:36,345
I was the other party in his assault case.

338
00:18:37,596 --> 00:18:39,598
I paid a settlement,
so my case was dropped.

339
00:18:39,682 --> 00:18:43,394
Are you saying you paid
to weasel your way out of this?

340
00:18:43,936 --> 00:18:45,187
To leave me high and dry?

341
00:18:45,271 --> 00:18:47,523
That's why it's always
better to have money.

342
00:18:47,606 --> 00:18:49,233
It's not too late to start trying.

343
00:18:49,316 --> 00:18:51,902
Although I'm not sure
you'll ever know what it's like.

344
00:18:52,403 --> 00:18:54,447
Hey, you can just stay out of this.

345
00:18:54,530 --> 00:18:57,700
Sir, let's just move this along.
We're all busy, aren't we?

346
00:18:57,783 --> 00:19:00,453
-Yes, let's move this along.
-What?

347
00:19:00,536 --> 00:19:01,787
Please file this as well.

348
00:19:01,871 --> 00:19:03,122
What? Okay.

349
00:19:04,749 --> 00:19:06,041
Let's proceed with a countersuit.

350
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:07,668
Breach of standard labor contract.

351
00:19:07,752 --> 00:19:10,337
I discovered you were in charge
of managing the extras.

352
00:19:10,421 --> 00:19:11,547
Just like your arm,

353
00:19:11,630 --> 00:19:14,049
Ms. Shin suffered severe health issues.

354
00:19:17,928 --> 00:19:20,973
Evidenced by her vomiting live on air,
currently under regulatory review.

355
00:19:21,056 --> 00:19:23,559
And on top of that,
there are unpaid wages.

356
00:19:23,642 --> 00:19:26,020
Should I just sue the entire network?

357
00:19:26,103 --> 00:19:26,979
What?

358
00:19:27,062 --> 00:19:29,106
There's no reason
to blow this up like that.

359
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:30,941
This is strictly a personal matter.

360
00:19:31,025 --> 00:19:32,318
You're right.

361
00:19:32,401 --> 00:19:33,861
So the network's the problem.

362
00:19:33,944 --> 00:19:36,322
How about we file a joint lawsuit?

363
00:19:37,198 --> 00:19:41,035
I'm no stranger to either side
of a legal battle.

364
00:19:52,505 --> 00:19:53,464
Why you…

365
00:20:00,596 --> 00:20:01,680
Cha Se-gye.

366
00:20:02,389 --> 00:20:04,809
Did you rush over here
because you were worried about me?

367
00:20:04,892 --> 00:20:07,394
No. I didn't come because I was worried.

368
00:20:09,146 --> 00:20:11,941
The contractee owes
a duty of care to the contractor.

369
00:20:12,024 --> 00:20:14,360
And this is practically next door

370
00:20:14,902 --> 00:20:16,111
to my place.

371
00:20:16,987 --> 00:20:18,614
"Practically next door"?

372
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,533
I see.

373
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,743
So are we what they call
"neighbor-cousins,"

374
00:20:22,827 --> 00:20:25,037
who can often feel closer to you
than blood relatives?

375
00:20:25,663 --> 00:20:26,914
Neighbor-cousins? As if.

376
00:20:26,997 --> 00:20:29,500
Do you even know the property value gap
between our neighborhoods?

377
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:31,210
Always with that coy back-and-forth.

378
00:20:31,293 --> 00:20:32,628
I know what is in your heart.

379
00:20:32,711 --> 00:20:35,381
You came because you were worried
and missed me, right?

380
00:20:35,464 --> 00:20:38,676
It's like you make a hobby
of twisting things to make it seem like

381
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:39,885
I worry about you.

382
00:20:39,969 --> 00:20:41,011
Oh, all right.

383
00:20:41,554 --> 00:20:44,348
It was that coyness that led me
to mistake your true intentions.

384
00:20:44,431 --> 00:20:45,808
I shall not mind it at all.

385
00:20:50,312 --> 00:20:51,856
And what's with the dog?

386
00:20:51,939 --> 00:20:53,148
Just a dog I found.

387
00:20:53,232 --> 00:20:54,149
Don't tell me.

388
00:20:54,817 --> 00:20:56,694
You can't keep it in that windowless room.

389
00:20:56,777 --> 00:20:58,946
-That is no concern of yours.
-Such a busybody.

390
00:20:59,029 --> 00:21:00,364
Dogs are for life, you know.

391
00:21:00,447 --> 00:21:02,908
You shouldn't pick up a stray
if you can't commit.

392
00:21:04,118 --> 00:21:07,079
Fine, keep it or don't.
Do whatever you want.

393
00:21:07,162 --> 00:21:10,332
Shin Seo-ri, before we enter
into this contract,

394
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:12,042
let's set one ground rule first.

395
00:21:12,626 --> 00:21:14,753
-Go on.
-From now on, let's be sure to keep

396
00:21:14,837 --> 00:21:16,922
our professional
and personal lives separate.

397
00:21:17,006 --> 00:21:19,300
Whether by social class or by status,

398
00:21:19,383 --> 00:21:22,386
we have absolutely no business
getting mixed up like this.

399
00:21:22,469 --> 00:21:24,221
That should not be an issue for me.

400
00:21:25,139 --> 00:21:26,181
However,

401
00:21:26,891 --> 00:21:28,058
I <i>am</i> worried about you.

402
00:21:30,144 --> 00:21:33,689
You will be absolutely itching to see me
in a more personal capacity.

403
00:21:33,772 --> 00:21:35,065
Think you can resist?

404
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:40,946
You know, this conversation took
a mighty wrong turn earlier.

405
00:21:41,030 --> 00:21:42,656
What kind of delusional thought process

406
00:21:42,740 --> 00:21:45,576
leads you to conclude that I'd long
for someone like you?

407
00:21:45,659 --> 00:21:47,036
Then let us do this.

408
00:21:47,119 --> 00:21:49,580
Since you are worried
about this dog living in a room

409
00:21:49,663 --> 00:21:50,748
without windows,

410
00:21:50,831 --> 00:21:53,167
and I wish to give you a gift in return,

411
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:54,793
we can simply make an exchange.

412
00:21:54,877 --> 00:21:56,003
"Gift in return"?

413
00:21:57,630 --> 00:21:59,673
"Exchange"? You're not making any sense.

414
00:22:01,425 --> 00:22:03,761
By any chance,
does that older brother of yours

415
00:22:04,261 --> 00:22:06,722
-visit your home often?
-"Brother"? Who?

416
00:22:08,432 --> 00:22:09,725
Choi Mun-do?

417
00:22:09,808 --> 00:22:11,769
Why the hell would he come to my house?

418
00:22:20,694 --> 00:22:24,031
You know, she just showed up
unfazed with her dog.

419
00:22:24,114 --> 00:22:25,950
I explained to the police

420
00:22:26,033 --> 00:22:28,911
that I planned to claim full compensation,
emotional damages included.

421
00:22:28,994 --> 00:22:29,995
As I was doing that,

422
00:22:30,079 --> 00:22:32,206
Mr. Cha Se-gye showed up,
just as you predicted.

423
00:22:32,289 --> 00:22:35,042
He even had the charges
against Shin Seo-ri dropped.

424
00:22:35,125 --> 00:22:36,335
<i>Biojei Entertainment?</i>

425
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:41,382
After recruiting Shin Seo-ri,
an obscure actress, Mr. Cha is looking

426
00:22:41,465 --> 00:22:42,925
to acquire her agency as well.

427
00:22:43,008 --> 00:22:47,054
A late-night trip to the police station
and a sudden agency acquisition.

428
00:22:48,222 --> 00:22:49,098
How amusing.

429
00:22:49,181 --> 00:22:52,059
Se-gye keeps creating
more leverage for me all on his own.

430
00:22:52,685 --> 00:22:54,895
Despite being family,
it seems he is not someone

431
00:22:54,979 --> 00:22:56,522
you welcome into your home.

432
00:22:57,731 --> 00:22:58,816
"He"?

433
00:23:02,277 --> 00:23:04,113
Why do you keep asking about Choi Mun-do?

434
00:23:04,196 --> 00:23:06,949
What, is he your type or something?

435
00:23:08,575 --> 00:23:09,576
My "type"?

436
00:23:11,370 --> 00:23:12,955
He may seem like a good man,

437
00:23:13,038 --> 00:23:15,290
but don't be fooled by his appearance.

438
00:23:16,375 --> 00:23:17,584
He's totally two-faced.

439
00:23:17,668 --> 00:23:21,046
He's the type to smile
while stabbing you in the back.

440
00:23:24,842 --> 00:23:27,636
<i>Bull's-eye!</i>

441
00:23:32,391 --> 00:23:35,310
The Crown Prince must have been
born with a divine gift for archery.

442
00:23:35,394 --> 00:23:37,354
Every shot he takes is a bull's-eye.

443
00:23:39,982 --> 00:23:42,234
-It's a pheasant!
-Look, a pheasant!

444
00:23:47,448 --> 00:23:50,242
Bull's-eye!

445
00:23:50,325 --> 00:23:52,327
Did His Highness hit the pheasant?

446
00:23:52,411 --> 00:23:53,746
That is not all he can hit.

447
00:23:53,829 --> 00:23:56,665
He hunts any wild animal
that roams near the rear garden.

448
00:23:59,418 --> 00:24:00,544
Wild animals?

449
00:24:10,763 --> 00:24:11,930
Go away!

450
00:24:12,431 --> 00:24:14,141
Run far away from the palace!

451
00:24:17,603 --> 00:24:18,562
Go!

452
00:24:19,313 --> 00:24:21,315
Do not ever come near here again.

453
00:24:21,899 --> 00:24:22,941
Go!

454
00:25:03,023 --> 00:25:05,025
Just because you act all high and mighty

455
00:25:05,109 --> 00:25:08,028
doesn't mean you suddenly gain authority.

456
00:25:08,862 --> 00:25:11,156
True charisma…

457
00:25:12,658 --> 00:25:14,201
comes from actual ability…

458
00:25:15,577 --> 00:25:16,912
you know what I mean?

459
00:25:16,995 --> 00:25:17,871
All right.

460
00:25:17,955 --> 00:25:19,873
Seeing how you so openly speak ill of him,

461
00:25:19,957 --> 00:25:21,834
it seems you two are on poor terms.

462
00:25:22,334 --> 00:25:24,169
He will certainly never visit.

463
00:25:24,253 --> 00:25:25,420
Excellent.

464
00:25:28,132 --> 00:25:29,216
Cha Se-gye.

465
00:25:29,299 --> 00:25:31,301
I give you this dog as a gift in return.

466
00:25:31,802 --> 00:25:34,012
I do not have the money
to buy luxury goods,

467
00:25:34,096 --> 00:25:35,514
and I have no letter for you,

468
00:25:35,597 --> 00:25:37,349
so I shall entrust this dog to you.

469
00:25:38,225 --> 00:25:41,103
Think of him as an extension of me,
and take good care of him.

470
00:25:41,186 --> 00:25:42,855
Are you nuts? Why would I…

471
00:25:45,065 --> 00:25:48,694
This dog will be more comfortable
in your home than in my windowless one.

472
00:25:48,777 --> 00:25:49,862
Here.

473
00:25:50,571 --> 00:25:52,906
I am counting on you, Cha Se-gye.

474
00:25:59,580 --> 00:26:00,497
Hey!

475
00:26:00,998 --> 00:26:02,291
Hey, Shin Seo-ri!

476
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,710
I'm allergic to dogs!

477
00:26:05,836 --> 00:26:06,712
Hey!

478
00:26:07,838 --> 00:26:09,006
Damn it.

479
00:26:09,673 --> 00:26:11,675
Stop wagging your tail. You're shedding.

480
00:26:12,551 --> 00:26:14,219
When was your last bath?

481
00:26:16,763 --> 00:26:17,973
You stink.

482
00:26:19,892 --> 00:26:21,602
You're so loud. Be quiet.

483
00:26:22,311 --> 00:26:24,396
Quiet! Be quiet!

484
00:26:30,402 --> 00:26:33,614
Anyway, you'll be out of here by tomorrow.

485
00:26:36,116 --> 00:26:37,451
I have fur all over me.

486
00:26:40,245 --> 00:26:41,496
God, it's so itchy.

487
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:43,248
So itchy. Damn it.

488
00:26:43,332 --> 00:26:45,459
Seriously? All because
of that crazy woman.

489
00:26:46,418 --> 00:26:47,920
Damn it.

490
00:26:48,545 --> 00:26:50,172
Should I just kick it out now?

491
00:26:50,255 --> 00:26:51,298
What?

492
00:26:51,924 --> 00:26:53,258
You kicked the dog out?

493
00:26:53,884 --> 00:26:55,594
A man who poisons everything he touches.

494
00:26:55,677 --> 00:26:58,096
A thousand cuts and being torn limb
from limb would not suffice!

495
00:26:58,180 --> 00:27:00,766
May you rot and die a painful death!

496
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:09,775
Damn it.

497
00:27:09,858 --> 00:27:12,694
Even just imagining it makes me sick.

498
00:27:14,154 --> 00:27:17,449
God only knows what she'd do to me
if I just dumped it somewhere.

499
00:27:19,243 --> 00:27:21,119
I should get rid of it properly.

500
00:27:28,919 --> 00:27:30,128
Living alone must get lonely.

501
00:27:30,212 --> 00:27:32,339
It's a gift for you. Take it.

502
00:27:32,422 --> 00:27:33,298
Thank you so much.

503
00:27:33,382 --> 00:27:35,133
It's a bit too dirty for a gift.

504
00:27:35,217 --> 00:27:36,426
Then consider it a mission.

505
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:37,886
Just get it out of my sight.

506
00:27:37,970 --> 00:27:40,764
You're allergic to dog fur.
Why did you bring it home?

507
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:44,226
You can clearly tell it's a stray.

508
00:27:44,309 --> 00:27:46,520
I didn't find it. Someone forced it on me.

509
00:27:46,603 --> 00:27:49,231
But you're not one to be saddled
with something against your will.

510
00:27:49,314 --> 00:27:50,857
-Who was it?
-You don't need to know.

511
00:27:50,941 --> 00:27:53,110
Anyway, get rid of this dog today.

512
00:27:54,152 --> 00:27:55,612
Or just raise it yourself.

513
00:27:56,363 --> 00:27:58,198
Sir, I can't take the dog either.

514
00:27:58,282 --> 00:28:00,534
My Min-ji is very picky.

515
00:28:03,912 --> 00:28:05,247
Min-ji?

516
00:28:05,330 --> 00:28:06,665
Is Min-ji your girlfriend?

517
00:28:06,748 --> 00:28:08,417
Min-ji is the name of my cat.

518
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,085
You wouldn't know
because you don't care,

519
00:28:10,168 --> 00:28:11,837
but I've been a cat owner for ten years.

520
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:13,213
Then find it a home.

521
00:28:13,297 --> 00:28:15,215
Pets are popular these days, right?

522
00:28:15,299 --> 00:28:18,176
Well, the chances of a full-grown,
mixed-breed dog like this

523
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:20,804
-getting adopted aren't good.
-So what should I do?

524
00:28:20,887 --> 00:28:22,472
You want me to continue living with it?

525
00:28:22,556 --> 00:28:25,892
You poor thing.
Of all people, <i>he</i> had to find you.

526
00:28:30,272 --> 00:28:32,399
I arranged this gathering
to mark a new beginning.

527
00:28:32,482 --> 00:28:34,443
As a family, we should clear the air.

528
00:28:34,526 --> 00:28:35,819
What is there to eat?

529
00:28:35,902 --> 00:28:38,155
This is practically an empty plate.

530
00:28:38,238 --> 00:28:39,990
Such poor hospitality. My goodness.

531
00:28:52,377 --> 00:28:53,420
Why, this is

532
00:28:53,503 --> 00:28:55,088
the ultimate land-and-sea delicacy

533
00:28:55,172 --> 00:28:57,090
where the vitality
freshly drawn from the ocean

534
00:28:57,174 --> 00:28:59,259
is combined with the spirit of Mount Jiri

535
00:28:59,324 --> 00:29:01,033
to achieve a sublime harmony of opposites.

536
00:29:01,126 --> 00:29:03,555
DIVINE FLAVORS

537
00:29:03,638 --> 00:29:06,558
It seems our Seo-ri
has a real knack for mukbang.

538
00:29:06,641 --> 00:29:08,643
We should get you on a food show too.

539
00:29:09,353 --> 00:29:11,063
"Our Seo-ri"? Since when?

540
00:29:11,146 --> 00:29:13,190
Oh, right. Director Kim called yesterday.

541
00:29:13,273 --> 00:29:16,109
You've been cast
in <i>The Women's Kingdom Season 2.</i>

542
00:29:16,193 --> 00:29:19,154
Since it's a new season,
they said they needed a new face.

543
00:29:19,237 --> 00:29:20,864
So I got you a spot, Seo-ri.

544
00:29:21,531 --> 00:29:23,784
Ma'am. How could you make
such a decision

545
00:29:23,867 --> 00:29:24,868
without even telling me?

546
00:29:24,951 --> 00:29:28,497
Why would I need to consult you
for a minor supporting role?

547
00:29:29,081 --> 00:29:30,415
Are you done?

548
00:29:30,499 --> 00:29:32,417
That yellow part was the most delicious.

549
00:29:32,501 --> 00:29:33,502
You eat it.

550
00:29:35,128 --> 00:29:36,380
Then I will not refuse.

551
00:29:38,757 --> 00:29:40,300
My, you have a healthy appetite.

552
00:29:40,384 --> 00:29:41,593
So healthy.

553
00:29:53,730 --> 00:29:55,440
Quality over quantity, I see.

554
00:29:55,524 --> 00:29:58,527
I must succeed
so I can eat that for every meal.

555
00:30:01,363 --> 00:30:02,364
NEW MESSAGE

556
00:30:06,576 --> 00:30:08,912
<i>Binge-watch Season 1 before the meeting.</i>

557
00:30:08,995 --> 00:30:12,165
<i>While you're at it,</i>
<i>analyze the trends of other hit shows.</i>

558
00:30:12,249 --> 00:30:14,876
<i>You're probably rusty</i>
<i>after your long break.</i>

559
00:30:15,585 --> 00:30:18,422
How could I even be rusty
when I am just getting started?

560
00:30:19,464 --> 00:30:21,258
Seeing is believing, I suppose.

561
00:30:21,341 --> 00:30:22,968
Hey! Seriously.

562
00:30:23,051 --> 00:30:24,845
You're talking over Ji-hyo.

563
00:30:24,928 --> 00:30:26,471
Please be quiet.

564
00:30:27,639 --> 00:30:29,766
You have turned to stone
in that very spot.

565
00:30:30,559 --> 00:30:31,935
Is it that entertaining?

566
00:30:32,561 --> 00:30:35,021
There's nothing like a drama
to escape reality.

567
00:30:35,105 --> 00:30:36,773
Your reality seems pretty tough too.

568
00:30:36,857 --> 00:30:38,150
Maybe you should binge-watch it.

569
00:30:38,233 --> 00:30:41,278
I saw her playing the queen.
Her acting was insufferably vulgar.

570
00:30:43,113 --> 00:30:45,282
What do you know about acting?

571
00:30:54,791 --> 00:30:55,834
Jeez.

572
00:31:06,636 --> 00:31:07,888
Unit 203?

573
00:31:17,772 --> 00:31:21,401
My, this "binge-watching" business
is truly captivating.

574
00:31:21,485 --> 00:31:25,238
Once you start,
you forget to even eat or drink.

575
00:31:25,989 --> 00:31:26,907
…PALACE INTRIGUES

576
00:31:26,990 --> 00:31:27,866
ASSASSINATIONS…

577
00:31:27,949 --> 00:31:29,784
Did you need to go this hard?

578
00:31:29,868 --> 00:31:31,953
Besides binge-watching,

579
00:31:32,037 --> 00:31:34,539
I was told to analyze "the trends."

580
00:31:36,458 --> 00:31:38,168
Is there anything else?

581
00:31:38,251 --> 00:31:39,377
No?

582
00:31:40,504 --> 00:31:42,714
SANDGLASS

583
00:31:42,797 --> 00:31:44,591
<i>I thought I could have you this way.</i>

584
00:31:44,674 --> 00:31:45,842
-Jeez.
<i>-You're my woman.</i>

585
00:31:45,926 --> 00:31:48,136
He really does not understand women.

586
00:31:48,220 --> 00:31:50,263
He would scare away any woman.

587
00:31:50,347 --> 00:31:52,098
<i>Impotent?</i>

588
00:31:52,182 --> 00:31:54,184
<i>How could I be impotent?</i>

589
00:31:54,267 --> 00:31:55,894
-"Impotent."
<i>-What are you talking about?</i>

590
00:31:55,977 --> 00:31:57,938
-"Impotent!"
<i>-How could I be impotent?</i>

591
00:31:58,563 --> 00:32:00,815
<i>How? How could I be impotent?</i>

592
00:32:00,899 --> 00:32:02,734
As if being impotent was a big deal.

593
00:32:03,276 --> 00:32:06,947
The eunuchs could not fool around,
but they lived large and lavishly.

594
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:08,657
LADIES OF THE PALACE

595
00:32:08,740 --> 00:32:11,117
<i>You went between the Queen</i>
<i>and the concubines</i>

596
00:32:11,201 --> 00:32:13,078
<i>to intentionally sow discord?</i>

597
00:32:21,044 --> 00:32:23,380
It has been ages since I heard
such a gratifying thrashing.

598
00:32:23,463 --> 00:32:25,340
It is simply music to my ears!

599
00:32:26,132 --> 00:32:27,467
There you go.

600
00:32:27,551 --> 00:32:28,969
She's actually laughing at that.

601
00:32:29,052 --> 00:32:30,762
You are amazing!

602
00:32:31,596 --> 00:32:32,722
My goodness.

603
00:32:36,726 --> 00:32:39,813
Since that obstinate man even took in
Young Master Dog,

604
00:32:39,896 --> 00:32:42,440
I shall take this chance
to properly thank him.

605
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,661
Hey, Unit 203. You know your <i>hanja.</i>

606
00:32:54,744 --> 00:32:57,247
I happen to be quite gifted
in classical verse.

607
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:02,502
Wait. "One…" Gosh.

608
00:33:03,044 --> 00:33:04,170
Who is this for anyway?

609
00:33:04,254 --> 00:33:06,381
As my funds for luxury goods are lacking,

610
00:33:06,464 --> 00:33:10,093
I intend to give this handwritten letter
to my fan as a gift in reverse.

611
00:33:10,176 --> 00:33:11,428
A fan?

612
00:33:11,511 --> 00:33:14,014
I thought you were unknown.
You have a fan now?

613
00:33:14,097 --> 00:33:17,392
Of course. Se-gye is the only one
who worries about me.

614
00:33:23,422 --> 00:33:25,062
That concludes the contract signing.

615
00:33:25,149 --> 00:33:26,776
Once the remaining purchase balance

616
00:33:26,860 --> 00:33:28,903
and Ms. Shin's signing bonus
are deposited,

617
00:33:28,987 --> 00:33:30,530
you will officially become a subsidiary.

618
00:33:30,614 --> 00:33:32,741
Let's get this project moving quickly.

619
00:33:32,824 --> 00:33:35,702
The marketing team will send over
the ad proposal this week,

620
00:33:35,785 --> 00:33:37,245
so give us your feedback right away.

621
00:33:37,329 --> 00:33:39,039
Yes, of course.

622
00:33:40,206 --> 00:33:41,499
Wait, Mr. Cha.

623
00:33:41,583 --> 00:33:43,960
Will we be taking a commemorative photo?

624
00:33:44,044 --> 00:33:45,128
-A photo?
-Yes.

625
00:33:46,421 --> 00:33:49,215
Okay, say cheese. One, two, three.

626
00:33:51,676 --> 00:33:52,761
Good work, everyone.

627
00:33:53,511 --> 00:33:55,805
Well, you must be very busy.

628
00:34:10,779 --> 00:34:12,072
Shin Seo-ri, what now?

629
00:34:15,408 --> 00:34:17,744
You knew it was me just from my footsteps?

630
00:34:19,079 --> 00:34:20,538
You have a serious problem.

631
00:34:21,164 --> 00:34:23,166
What now? What do you want?

632
00:34:26,998 --> 00:34:28,724
You have been sniffling since earlier.

633
00:34:28,799 --> 00:34:31,383
Is your body not hardy enough
to avoid a measly little cold?

634
00:34:31,466 --> 00:34:33,385
Thanks to a certain someone, I'm a mess.

635
00:34:33,468 --> 00:34:35,345
I've had a runny nose
for over a week now.

636
00:34:35,428 --> 00:34:36,304
Yes.

637
00:34:36,805 --> 00:34:38,556
As it is, I owe you a great deal.

638
00:34:38,640 --> 00:34:41,184
So I wanted to take this chance
to thank you properly.

639
00:34:42,977 --> 00:34:44,729
Here, take it.

640
00:34:45,438 --> 00:34:46,856
What's this? A legal notice?

641
00:34:46,940 --> 00:34:48,233
A missive.

642
00:34:48,316 --> 00:34:49,818
I mean, a handwritten letter.

643
00:34:51,778 --> 00:34:52,946
-A letter?
-Yes.

644
00:34:53,029 --> 00:34:54,239
For me?

645
00:34:57,283 --> 00:34:59,869
It is a letter expressing my gratitude,

646
00:34:59,953 --> 00:35:02,956
so be sure to read it alone tonight
before you go to sleep.

647
00:35:23,810 --> 00:35:25,979
It really is a missive. <i>Hanja </i>and all.

648
00:35:29,858 --> 00:35:30,942
<i>"Jak."</i>

649
00:35:33,319 --> 00:35:34,946
Is she messing with me? Damn it.

650
00:35:52,255 --> 00:35:54,174
<i>How did you fare last night?</i>

651
00:35:55,341 --> 00:35:59,053
<i>By a sunlit window,</i>
<i>my fondness for you grows.</i>

652
00:36:00,180 --> 00:36:03,516
<i>If the traces of my visits in your dreams</i>
<i>were left as a fragrance,</i>

653
00:36:04,559 --> 00:36:08,229
<i>the green garden before your door</i>
<i>would be full of butterflies.</i>

654
00:36:08,313 --> 00:36:10,273
What does this even mean?

655
00:36:13,902 --> 00:36:16,112
Someone might mistake this
for a love letter.

656
00:36:25,872 --> 00:36:27,582
Hey! You little son of a…

657
00:36:29,793 --> 00:36:32,045
Is it because
you're from the streets?

658
00:36:32,128 --> 00:36:34,756
You try to snatch
anything that drops to the floor.

659
00:36:34,839 --> 00:36:36,883
You'll get a tummy ache, you punk.

660
00:36:37,675 --> 00:36:39,636
Damn it. Gross.

661
00:37:03,284 --> 00:37:05,036
"Amazing."

662
00:37:06,830 --> 00:37:08,122
MY AMAZING FAN

663
00:37:08,748 --> 00:37:09,833
"My…"

664
00:37:12,669 --> 00:37:13,837
"My man"?

665
00:37:19,717 --> 00:37:21,886
"My…

666
00:37:23,471 --> 00:37:24,806
amazing…

667
00:37:25,974 --> 00:37:27,100
fan."

668
00:37:27,183 --> 00:37:28,601
"My man"?

669
00:37:44,367 --> 00:37:46,077
This woman is in love with me.

670
00:38:01,634 --> 00:38:03,136
My goodness.

671
00:38:03,219 --> 00:38:05,638
What an incredible view.

672
00:38:05,722 --> 00:38:07,348
You have a job now.

673
00:38:07,432 --> 00:38:09,934
Why stay in that windowless room
any longer?

674
00:38:10,018 --> 00:38:12,645
You have the deposit money now,
and the rent will be the same.

675
00:38:12,729 --> 00:38:15,523
Not to mention, you'll have
the whole floor to yourself.

676
00:38:15,607 --> 00:38:18,526
Absolutely.
A place like this is a total steal.

677
00:38:18,610 --> 00:38:19,777
A total steal.

678
00:38:19,861 --> 00:38:21,571
The view is quite refreshing.

679
00:38:21,654 --> 00:38:22,614
This will do.

680
00:38:23,239 --> 00:38:24,574
Even a yard to run around in.

681
00:38:24,657 --> 00:38:25,909
A new residence

682
00:38:25,992 --> 00:38:28,411
calls for a proper ritual.
It has been a while.

683
00:38:31,581 --> 00:38:33,416
Regarding the first draft
of the Dynaestie ad,

684
00:38:33,499 --> 00:38:35,043
her agency's response has been positive.

685
00:38:35,126 --> 00:38:37,420
A few details need tweaking
before it goes to the ad agency,

686
00:38:37,503 --> 00:38:40,298
but we should be able to see a preview
by the end of the month.

687
00:38:40,381 --> 00:38:41,633
Okay.

688
00:38:43,051 --> 00:38:44,177
Hey, Mr. Son.

689
00:38:45,678 --> 00:38:48,181
Have you ever received a love letter?

690
00:38:48,264 --> 00:38:49,599
A love letter?

691
00:38:50,308 --> 00:38:52,226
I've been dumped plenty of times.

692
00:38:52,310 --> 00:38:54,562
Wait, I got a note from a Secret Santa

693
00:38:55,063 --> 00:38:55,980
in elementary school.

694
00:38:56,064 --> 00:38:57,148
No, not like that.

695
00:38:57,231 --> 00:39:00,485
I mean a handwritten letter.
One that the sender personally wrote.

696
00:39:02,862 --> 00:39:04,072
Why do you ask?

697
00:39:04,906 --> 00:39:07,158
Did someone profess their love for you?

698
00:39:07,241 --> 00:39:08,493
No.

699
00:39:08,576 --> 00:39:09,661
Of course not.

700
00:39:09,744 --> 00:39:11,746
When did I say that?

701
00:39:11,829 --> 00:39:12,747
I'm just curious.

702
00:39:12,830 --> 00:39:14,332
And why are you so curious?

703
00:39:14,415 --> 00:39:17,377
I need to know why you're asking
so I can answer properly.

704
00:39:17,460 --> 00:39:18,962
Just because.

705
00:39:19,629 --> 00:39:22,924
I was wondering what the intention is
when people give love letters.

706
00:39:23,007 --> 00:39:26,010
There's no hidden intention.
They're just sharing how they feel.

707
00:39:28,346 --> 00:39:29,472
Feelings.

708
00:39:29,555 --> 00:39:31,015
Not everything in this world

709
00:39:31,099 --> 00:39:33,309
has dark ulterior motives

710
00:39:33,393 --> 00:39:35,269
and conspiracies lurking underneath.

711
00:39:35,353 --> 00:39:36,646
This world

712
00:39:36,729 --> 00:39:39,357
is far more filled with humanity
than you think, sir.

713
00:39:40,441 --> 00:39:44,112
So what? Are you saying
I always have dark ulterior motives?

714
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:54,539
How long must I handle
these menial tasks myself?

715
00:39:54,622 --> 00:39:56,582
My graceful hands are getting calluses.

716
00:39:57,875 --> 00:40:00,545
Delicate jade hands are
the very foundation of refinement.

717
00:40:00,628 --> 00:40:02,130
I need to start taking care of them.

718
00:40:03,673 --> 00:40:04,632
Damn it.

719
00:40:14,058 --> 00:40:16,269
This should be good enough
to bring a dog home.

720
00:40:16,352 --> 00:40:18,104
SHRINE OF DOG

721
00:40:26,154 --> 00:40:27,238
Hey, Unit 203.

722
00:40:27,321 --> 00:40:28,531
I mean, Rooftop.

723
00:40:28,614 --> 00:40:31,534
Why aren't you answering your phone? Huh?

724
00:40:31,617 --> 00:40:33,494
-What is that?
-Jeez.

725
00:40:33,578 --> 00:40:35,788
Your grandmother must be busy.

726
00:40:35,872 --> 00:40:37,707
She had it delivered this time.

727
00:40:38,374 --> 00:40:41,210
I brought it up so it wouldn't go bad.

728
00:40:41,961 --> 00:40:43,921
SENDER: NAM OK-SUN

729
00:40:55,808 --> 00:40:57,894
<i>Seo-ri, you got the storyboard, right?</i>

730
00:40:57,977 --> 00:40:59,604
The concept is very avant-garde,

731
00:40:59,687 --> 00:41:00,605
and it's got

732
00:41:00,688 --> 00:41:03,441
<i>that trendy Gen Z style.</i>
<i>It's kitschy and well-executed.</i>

733
00:41:03,524 --> 00:41:05,109
<i>Mr. Cha has good taste.</i>

734
00:41:05,193 --> 00:41:09,155
<i>The shooting schedule will be out soon,</i>
<i>so really focus on your skincare regimen.</i>

735
00:41:09,238 --> 00:41:12,200
<i>There are so many great options now.</i>
<i>Glutathione shots, whitening injections.</i>

736
00:41:12,283 --> 00:41:14,327
What is there to take special care of?

737
00:41:14,410 --> 00:41:15,912
I was born with flawless skin.

738
00:41:15,995 --> 00:41:18,790
Put the same fire you came at me with
into your skincare.

739
00:41:18,873 --> 00:41:22,210
And you're booked for <i>Jane Asks,</i>
the YouTube show, on the day of the shoot.

740
00:41:22,293 --> 00:41:25,088
<i>Play up the sob story about your hardships</i>
<i>as an unknown actress.</i>

741
00:41:25,171 --> 00:41:27,590
<i>Pile on the sorrow and sentiment</i>
<i>to make it a tearjerker.</i>

742
00:41:34,222 --> 00:41:35,765
But I do not know anything

743
00:41:36,682 --> 00:41:38,184
about this woman.

744
00:41:47,110 --> 00:41:49,487
NAM OK-SUN
17 YEONSOLRO 8-GIL, SONGJIN

745
00:41:56,327 --> 00:41:59,956
Sir, your cough has been bad lately.
Are you taking medicine?

746
00:42:00,039 --> 00:42:01,541
Medicine for a little cough?

747
00:42:02,708 --> 00:42:04,961
It's an issue
you could resolve quite quickly.

748
00:42:05,711 --> 00:42:08,214
Sir, that's already been taken care of.

749
00:42:11,175 --> 00:42:12,468
<i>I posted online,</i>

750
00:42:12,552 --> 00:42:14,637
<i>and the dog's owner called right away.</i>

751
00:42:16,097 --> 00:42:17,223
Really? That's great.

752
00:42:17,306 --> 00:42:19,559
Secretary Kim should be returning it
to the owner now.

753
00:42:19,642 --> 00:42:21,894
You can sleep peacefully starting tonight.

754
00:42:22,812 --> 00:42:23,729
Already?

755
00:42:23,813 --> 00:42:27,024
The sooner we send it off,
the sooner your suffering ends.

756
00:42:27,108 --> 00:42:30,444
I hired cleaners to remove
every single trace.

757
00:42:30,987 --> 00:42:31,904
So don't worry.

758
00:42:31,988 --> 00:42:33,573
I'm so grateful.

759
00:42:34,991 --> 00:42:36,159
You know me.

760
00:42:37,869 --> 00:42:39,162
She's going to miss it.

761
00:42:43,624 --> 00:42:45,451
THE CHAIL SONGJIN RESORT
GROUNDBREAKING CEREMONY

762
00:42:45,601 --> 00:42:46,802
-Gosh. Chairman.
-Hey.

763
00:42:46,885 --> 00:42:48,595
-Welcome, sir.
-Thank you for your hard work.

764
00:42:48,654 --> 00:42:50,089
-Thank you.
-Hang in there.

765
00:42:50,173 --> 00:42:52,008
Thank you for working so hard.

766
00:42:52,091 --> 00:42:53,050
Oh, my.

767
00:42:53,134 --> 00:42:54,927
Did Father seriously bring him here?

768
00:42:55,678 --> 00:42:56,888
Is he going senile?

769
00:42:56,971 --> 00:42:58,723
They say time waits for no one.

770
00:42:58,806 --> 00:43:01,601
Even after all the trouble he caused,
he still dotes on his own blood.

771
00:43:01,684 --> 00:43:04,478
Ladies, people can overhear you.
You should be more careful.

772
00:43:04,562 --> 00:43:06,522
Mun-do, you seem pretty relaxed.

773
00:43:06,615 --> 00:43:09,192
Even after seeing this,
you can still be calm and philosophical?

774
00:43:09,275 --> 00:43:11,777
Come on, sis.
Have you ever seen Mun-do get angry?

775
00:43:11,861 --> 00:43:13,196
Why would I be angry?

776
00:43:13,905 --> 00:43:15,907
Especially when Uncle is so happy.

777
00:43:17,533 --> 00:43:20,328
Gosh, I really can't figure him out.

778
00:43:20,870 --> 00:43:22,747
Is he actually happy or just pretending?

779
00:43:22,830 --> 00:43:26,334
We will now break ground
for The Chail Songjin Resort.

780
00:43:27,126 --> 00:43:29,503
One, two, three!

781
00:43:29,587 --> 00:43:30,815
CHAIL E&amp;C, SONGJIN CITY…

782
00:43:34,008 --> 00:43:36,260
Please join me in a warm round of applause

783
00:43:36,344 --> 00:43:40,306
for Songjin City, Chail Resort,
and their bright futures.

784
00:43:43,100 --> 00:43:45,144
Thank you for always looking out for us.

785
00:43:45,228 --> 00:43:46,687
-It's my pleasure.
-Thank you.

786
00:43:46,771 --> 00:43:49,398
-Thank you so much.
-Once this project is completed…

787
00:43:49,482 --> 00:43:51,150
-Yes.
-…we'll have you back.

788
00:43:51,234 --> 00:43:52,818
-Thank you.
<i>-By any chance,</i>

789
00:43:53,444 --> 00:43:55,446
does that older brother of yours

790
00:43:55,529 --> 00:43:56,989
visit your home often?

791
00:43:57,073 --> 00:43:58,824
-Thank you.
-I look forward to it.

792
00:43:58,908 --> 00:44:00,534
Oh, my.

793
00:44:00,618 --> 00:44:02,453
-Thank you.
-Thank you so much.

794
00:44:04,163 --> 00:44:06,123
-I have high hopes.
-Exactly.

795
00:44:12,964 --> 00:44:16,384
So you go around meeting
aspiring starlets now?

796
00:44:17,134 --> 00:44:19,720
I have A-list stars
lining up for me as it is.

797
00:44:19,804 --> 00:44:21,138
What would I do with a starlet?

798
00:44:22,223 --> 00:44:23,432
Right?

799
00:44:24,934 --> 00:44:27,186
Mind your personal affairs carefully.

800
00:44:27,270 --> 00:44:29,355
Don't throw away everything you've built.

801
00:44:29,981 --> 00:44:31,315
Se-gye.

802
00:44:31,399 --> 00:44:34,110
Don't waste your time meddling.
Just focus on smiling.

803
00:44:34,193 --> 00:44:36,153
The only thing you've got going for you

804
00:44:36,237 --> 00:44:39,282
is the handsome face
you got from your mom.

805
00:44:39,365 --> 00:44:40,658
You know?

806
00:44:43,786 --> 00:44:45,538
-We'll be counting on you.
-Of course.

807
00:44:46,622 --> 00:44:49,333
-Congratulations, President Choi.
-Your first dig.

808
00:44:50,084 --> 00:44:51,627
Thank you so much for coming.

809
00:44:55,673 --> 00:44:57,216
What the hell?

810
00:44:58,384 --> 00:44:59,468
Hey.

811
00:45:01,470 --> 00:45:02,680
Watch your mouth

812
00:45:02,763 --> 00:45:04,598
before I smash that jaw of yours.

813
00:45:13,357 --> 00:45:16,402
SONGJIN CITY WELCOMES CHAIL RESORT!

814
00:45:19,113 --> 00:45:21,907
SEORI'S NOODLE SHOP

815
00:45:22,033 --> 00:45:23,367
OPEN

816
00:46:02,073 --> 00:46:04,283
Well, this feels a bit…

817
00:46:08,204 --> 00:46:09,246
Goodness me.

818
00:46:10,539 --> 00:46:11,540
Seo-ri!

819
00:46:11,624 --> 00:46:13,209
Oh my gosh, Seo-ri! You're here.

820
00:46:13,292 --> 00:46:14,710
Come here, my sweet girl.

821
00:46:15,294 --> 00:46:16,670
You're really here.

822
00:46:17,421 --> 00:46:18,381
Let me look at you.

823
00:46:18,464 --> 00:46:20,466
Why are you so skinny?

824
00:46:20,549 --> 00:46:22,843
I can't believe my sweet girl is here.

825
00:46:25,638 --> 00:46:29,475
If you'd called ahead,
I would've grilled some meat.

826
00:46:39,110 --> 00:46:41,946
The neighborhood looks deserted.
Everything is closed down.

827
00:46:43,197 --> 00:46:44,323
How is business?

828
00:46:44,407 --> 00:46:47,326
They say they're building some resort.

829
00:46:47,410 --> 00:46:50,037
Everyone just sold out
for a handful of cash.

830
00:46:50,663 --> 00:46:51,956
Just forget it.

831
00:46:52,665 --> 00:46:55,251
If they are offering you money,
you should sell too.

832
00:46:55,334 --> 00:46:56,961
-This work must be hard.
-Gosh.

833
00:46:57,044 --> 00:47:00,381
Why would I? I'm still perfectly healthy.

834
00:47:00,464 --> 00:47:02,299
I'll work as long as my body lets me.

835
00:47:02,383 --> 00:47:04,385
At my age, not working is like being dead.

836
00:47:05,344 --> 00:47:06,303
This here

837
00:47:06,887 --> 00:47:08,305
is where I'll lay my head to rest.

838
00:47:09,140 --> 00:47:12,226
I watched you grow up here
and sent you to school.

839
00:47:14,812 --> 00:47:17,940
No other place in the world
could give me this kind of peace.

840
00:47:18,023 --> 00:47:19,900
I mean, money isn't everything.

841
00:47:22,111 --> 00:47:23,612
<i>It was just the two of them.</i>

842
00:47:25,114 --> 00:47:27,533
<i>They never had any need</i>
<i>for worldly possessions.</i>

843
00:47:29,076 --> 00:47:30,536
Eat.

844
00:47:30,619 --> 00:47:32,246
<i>This is needless meddling.</i>

845
00:47:35,833 --> 00:47:36,876
<i>Get a grip.</i>

846
00:47:38,502 --> 00:47:40,171
<i>Just look out for yourself.</i>

847
00:47:41,172 --> 00:47:42,840
I have this interview

848
00:47:42,923 --> 00:47:45,092
-coming up, you see.
-Okay.

849
00:47:45,176 --> 00:47:47,511
I have to tell them
stories about my hardships

850
00:47:47,595 --> 00:47:48,971
and the pain of being a nobody.

851
00:47:49,054 --> 00:47:50,139
Stuff like that.

852
00:47:50,222 --> 00:47:51,807
Are you going to be on TV?

853
00:47:52,308 --> 00:47:54,059
What channel will it be on?

854
00:47:54,143 --> 00:47:56,312
I'll have to record that, you know?

855
00:47:56,395 --> 00:47:59,148
My childhood memories are a little hazy.

856
00:48:00,691 --> 00:48:02,109
What? You…

857
00:48:02,693 --> 00:48:04,737
don't remember your childhood?

858
00:48:05,571 --> 00:48:07,072
Well, you know,

859
00:48:07,656 --> 00:48:10,284
a lot of people forget
their childhood as they grow up.

860
00:48:10,367 --> 00:48:14,497
Come to think of it,
you have been talking strangely lately.

861
00:48:15,706 --> 00:48:19,793
You were the same way
after that accident when you almost died.

862
00:48:21,170 --> 00:48:22,630
Maybe you're sick again?

863
00:48:24,381 --> 00:48:25,508
Accident?

864
00:48:26,884 --> 00:48:28,844
Granny, we're back.

865
00:48:29,929 --> 00:48:31,764
Smells so good in here.

866
00:48:31,847 --> 00:48:32,848
Yeah.

867
00:48:36,727 --> 00:48:39,271
What did Mun-do say
to make you punch him?

868
00:48:39,355 --> 00:48:41,857
You'd better speak up
if you're hoping for any leniency.

869
00:48:41,941 --> 00:48:44,318
His face just pissed me off,
so I punched him.

870
00:48:45,110 --> 00:48:47,488
No matter how much you dislike him,
Mun-do is still our blood.

871
00:48:47,571 --> 00:48:49,448
Even with this resort project,

872
00:48:49,532 --> 00:48:52,159
there's a headache of a restaurant
standing in the way.

873
00:48:52,785 --> 00:48:54,745
Yes. That's it. That restaurant.

874
00:48:55,389 --> 00:48:57,003
Some old lady is refusing to budge.

875
00:48:57,083 --> 00:48:59,208
Mun-do's been working
day and night to take care of it.

876
00:48:59,291 --> 00:49:00,292
SEORI'S NOODLE SHOP

877
00:49:00,376 --> 00:49:03,212
How long are you going
to keep drifting alone like that?

878
00:49:03,295 --> 00:49:04,880
Are you never coming back?

879
00:49:06,257 --> 00:49:07,424
Now I'm even seeing things.

880
00:49:08,175 --> 00:49:09,426
What? What did you say?

881
00:49:10,803 --> 00:49:12,179
It's nothing.

882
00:49:26,735 --> 00:49:28,696
Granny, this is awful. Just awful.

883
00:49:29,321 --> 00:49:31,490
You can't run a restaurant
if you can't season.

884
00:49:36,036 --> 00:49:37,746
Even thugs live by a code.

885
00:49:37,830 --> 00:49:39,498
Wasting precious food like this?

886
00:49:40,416 --> 00:49:42,293
Were you born without parents!

887
00:49:42,376 --> 00:49:43,419
Seo-ri.

888
00:49:43,502 --> 00:49:45,588
Oh, right. She's…

889
00:49:45,671 --> 00:49:47,840
that granddaughter
who's acting in Seoul.

890
00:49:48,507 --> 00:49:50,175
Well, you're a feisty one, aren't you?

891
00:49:50,259 --> 00:49:52,219
You should help Granny understand.

892
00:49:52,303 --> 00:49:55,014
Nowadays, people hate
shameless holdouts like you.

893
00:49:55,097 --> 00:49:58,601
Hey! You think money is everything,
you rotten bastards?

894
00:49:59,602 --> 00:50:00,728
Seo-ri.

895
00:50:01,312 --> 00:50:02,855
I'll take care of this.

896
00:50:04,064 --> 00:50:06,025
Get inside, quick. Go on now.

897
00:50:06,567 --> 00:50:07,818
Now, now. Hey, Granny.

898
00:50:09,278 --> 00:50:10,863
She should know what's going on.

899
00:50:10,946 --> 00:50:12,781
She needs a reality check

900
00:50:12,865 --> 00:50:14,950
if she's still chasing
that pipe dream of acting,

901
00:50:15,034 --> 00:50:16,327
given her family situation.

902
00:50:17,036 --> 00:50:19,246
What did you just say, you bastard?

903
00:50:19,330 --> 00:50:21,248
You bastard! What did you say?

904
00:50:21,332 --> 00:50:23,334
Goodness me!

905
00:50:23,417 --> 00:50:24,501
Damn it.

906
00:50:25,294 --> 00:50:26,754
Pretty strong for an old lady.

907
00:50:26,837 --> 00:50:29,673
You got a lot of money?
Enough to pay my hospital bills? Damn it.

908
00:50:29,757 --> 00:50:32,259
Forget the money.
Let me just hold that hand.

909
00:50:32,343 --> 00:50:34,053
Still so fair. Granny's still got it.

910
00:50:34,136 --> 00:50:35,012
Hey.

911
00:50:38,932 --> 00:50:41,101
It's like you're begging for a beating.

912
00:50:43,437 --> 00:50:44,355
Damn it.

913
00:50:46,482 --> 00:50:47,399
Boss!

914
00:50:47,483 --> 00:50:48,567
-Boss!
-Boss!

915
00:50:48,651 --> 00:50:49,526
SEORI'S RUSTIC PERIOD

916
00:50:49,610 --> 00:50:50,986
-Listen up.
-Let go, damn it.

917
00:50:51,070 --> 00:50:52,655
We will never leave this place.

918
00:50:52,738 --> 00:50:55,366
And we have no intention
of bowing down to your boss.

919
00:50:56,241 --> 00:50:58,827
Because that would be the same
as bowing down to the Japanese.

920
00:50:58,911 --> 00:51:01,038
Boss? The Japanese?

921
00:51:01,121 --> 00:51:02,956
What the hell are you talking about?

922
00:51:04,958 --> 00:51:06,293
<i>Rustic Period,</i> Episode 18.

923
00:51:06,377 --> 00:51:09,088
The climactic episode
where Kim Du-han takes down Jebi.

924
00:51:09,588 --> 00:51:12,841
Since you all are acting just like
a bunch of street thugs,

925
00:51:13,425 --> 00:51:16,345
I, like Kim Du-han, will punish you all!

926
00:51:16,428 --> 00:51:19,181
So you're Kim Du-han now?

927
00:51:19,264 --> 00:51:20,391
Then I'm Gu Ma-jeok.

928
00:51:20,474 --> 00:51:21,684
Why, you little…

929
00:51:34,822 --> 00:51:37,366
-Boss!
-Boss!

930
00:51:37,449 --> 00:51:39,576
-Boss!
-Boss, you okay?

931
00:51:41,161 --> 00:51:43,497
What are you doing? Get her! Damn it!

932
00:52:12,860 --> 00:52:14,361
Seo-ri, he's got a knife!

933
00:52:22,703 --> 00:52:23,787
Cha Se-gye, what are you--

934
00:52:23,871 --> 00:52:25,706
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

935
00:52:26,749 --> 00:52:28,667
A cowardly sneak attack from behind?

936
00:52:29,585 --> 00:52:30,961
Why you…

937
00:52:31,044 --> 00:52:32,087
Oh, no.

938
00:52:42,014 --> 00:52:43,182
Cha Se-gye.

939
00:52:43,265 --> 00:52:45,768
Are you here because you were
worried about me again?

940
00:52:46,310 --> 00:52:47,311
No…

941
00:53:00,991 --> 00:53:02,159
Cha Se-gye.

942
00:53:02,242 --> 00:53:04,119
Did you read my handwritten letter?

943
00:53:04,203 --> 00:53:05,704
Yeah. I…

944
00:53:05,788 --> 00:53:07,331
And the dog?

945
00:53:07,414 --> 00:53:09,291
Is it eating and doing well?

946
00:53:09,958 --> 00:53:10,834
The dog?

947
00:53:11,502 --> 00:53:12,377
Yeah, it's fine.

948
00:53:13,045 --> 00:53:15,172
I have been meaning to reach out to you.

949
00:53:15,255 --> 00:53:16,256
Excellent timing.

950
00:53:16,340 --> 00:53:18,634
I've found a proper home now, you see.

951
00:53:19,384 --> 00:53:21,386
So I will no longer need to trouble you.

952
00:53:21,470 --> 00:53:23,096
I shall take the dog back.

953
00:53:23,180 --> 00:53:24,681
Well? Is that not great news?

954
00:53:29,478 --> 00:53:30,687
We found its owner.

955
00:53:31,438 --> 00:53:33,023
Turns out it wasn't a stray.

956
00:53:34,691 --> 00:53:35,692
You found its owner?

957
00:53:36,777 --> 00:53:38,487
Mr. Son posted about it online.

958
00:53:38,570 --> 00:53:39,988
Its owner came by right away.

959
00:53:41,698 --> 00:53:42,825
It's for the best.

960
00:53:42,908 --> 00:53:46,078
When I think about how much sleep
I lost over that damn dog…

961
00:53:49,289 --> 00:53:50,457
Thank you.

962
00:53:52,209 --> 00:53:53,085
What?

963
00:53:53,168 --> 00:53:55,587
I am very grateful to you.

964
00:53:55,671 --> 00:53:57,506
I know I said it in the letter,

965
00:53:57,589 --> 00:54:00,008
but I wanted to say it to you in person.

966
00:54:03,887 --> 00:54:06,056
You don't need to be so direct.

967
00:54:06,139 --> 00:54:07,808
I have met many people here,

968
00:54:07,891 --> 00:54:10,686
but you have been the kindest to me,
and I am most thankful.

969
00:54:12,271 --> 00:54:14,731
You must be the best fan in the world.

970
00:54:14,815 --> 00:54:15,941
Fan?

971
00:54:16,525 --> 00:54:17,776
What do you mean, a fan?

972
00:54:17,860 --> 00:54:19,152
Do not be embarrassed.

973
00:54:19,695 --> 00:54:21,488
I know you care about me as my fan.

974
00:54:21,572 --> 00:54:23,031
I am well aware of that fact.

975
00:54:24,241 --> 00:54:25,409
I'm a fan of who now?

976
00:54:25,492 --> 00:54:28,078
How can you say something
so egregious so easily?

977
00:54:28,161 --> 00:54:29,204
A fan?

978
00:54:29,288 --> 00:54:30,747
What's all this about?

979
00:54:30,831 --> 00:54:33,917
Grandpa, it's nothing.
Don't worry about it. You can just go.

980
00:54:34,001 --> 00:54:35,210
You're this lady's fan?

981
00:54:35,878 --> 00:54:38,088
-No--
-Who is she? Why are you her fan?

982
00:54:38,171 --> 00:54:39,298
Wealthy Man?

983
00:54:40,924 --> 00:54:43,719
Miss, how do you know my Se-gye?

984
00:54:46,054 --> 00:54:49,474
He is my one and only fan.
A very reassuring presence in my world.

985
00:54:50,142 --> 00:54:51,602
A fan? As if. No, that's not it…

986
00:54:52,227 --> 00:54:54,396
We just know each other professionally.

987
00:54:54,479 --> 00:54:55,814
But she says otherwise!

988
00:54:57,524 --> 00:54:59,693
What the hell
have you been doing out there?

989
00:54:59,776 --> 00:55:01,194
It's really not like that.

990
00:55:01,278 --> 00:55:04,281
She misunderstood after I took pity
on her and helped her out a few times.

991
00:55:04,364 --> 00:55:05,365
You pity me?

992
00:55:47,658 --> 00:55:49,159
I taught them a mighty lesson.

993
00:55:50,077 --> 00:55:51,662
They will stay away now.

994
00:55:54,373 --> 00:55:57,000
If they start lurking again,
let me know immediately.

995
00:55:57,960 --> 00:56:00,128
What's the point of raising
a granddaughter

996
00:56:00,212 --> 00:56:01,630
if not for times like these?

997
00:56:06,969 --> 00:56:07,886
I almost forgot.

998
00:56:08,929 --> 00:56:10,472
This is nothing special.

999
00:56:11,682 --> 00:56:13,266
Just some embroidered slippers.

1000
00:56:20,107 --> 00:56:21,108
Who…

1001
00:56:27,656 --> 00:56:28,615
are you?

1002
00:56:48,885 --> 00:56:50,012
Anyone home?

1003
00:57:04,693 --> 00:57:05,902
Look at this. I knew it.

1004
00:57:06,486 --> 00:57:09,197
So much for a deep cleaning.
Just sloppy at best.

1005
00:57:14,911 --> 00:57:16,038
<i>Thank you.</i>

1006
00:57:16,621 --> 00:57:19,249
I am very grateful to you.

1007
00:57:19,332 --> 00:57:20,959
I know I said it in the letter,

1008
00:57:21,043 --> 00:57:22,878
but I wanted to say it to you in person.

1009
00:57:24,963 --> 00:57:26,673
What does she take me for?

1010
00:57:26,757 --> 00:57:28,300
<i>He is my one and only fan.</i>

1011
00:57:28,383 --> 00:57:30,343
A very reassuring presence in my world.

1012
00:57:31,553 --> 00:57:34,056
Why did she have to go
and misunderstand like that?

1013
00:57:36,767 --> 00:57:38,226
It's making me feel bad.

1014
00:57:40,062 --> 00:57:41,563
You pity me?

1015
00:57:52,449 --> 00:57:54,409
Why did she have to make that face?

1016
00:57:55,202 --> 00:57:57,037
Now I'm worrying about her.

1017
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:03,335
It's a nice view, even at night.

1018
00:58:03,418 --> 00:58:05,670
I see why your grandmother
refuses to leave.

1019
00:58:06,171 --> 00:58:07,506
What brings you here?

1020
00:58:08,131 --> 00:58:09,800
No matter how nice the view may be,

1021
00:58:09,883 --> 00:58:12,719
leaving your grandmother alone
in a place like this

1022
00:58:12,803 --> 00:58:13,845
feels wrong.

1023
00:58:14,805 --> 00:58:16,807
Closing the restaurant
and moving her somewhere nice

1024
00:58:16,890 --> 00:58:18,683
would give you peace of mind too.

1025
00:58:20,352 --> 00:58:23,396
Trying the carrot
since the stick didn't work?

1026
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,607
No, that's not the main reason.

1027
00:58:26,942 --> 00:58:28,151
I came to cheer you on.

1028
00:58:28,235 --> 00:58:29,361
Cheer me on?

1029
00:58:32,489 --> 00:58:36,118
I know you and Se-gye
aren't anything yet.

1030
00:58:36,201 --> 00:58:39,121
But I think you two would make
a surprisingly good couple.

1031
00:58:41,748 --> 00:58:42,916
You came all this way,

1032
00:58:42,999 --> 00:58:45,669
this late at night, just to tell me that?

1033
00:58:45,752 --> 00:58:46,837
Ms. Shin.

1034
00:58:48,088 --> 00:58:50,382
You should be friends with Cha Se-gye.

1035
00:58:50,465 --> 00:58:52,342
Even better if you become his person.

1036
00:58:53,385 --> 00:58:55,804
And even better
if you decide to share a future.

1037
00:58:55,887 --> 00:58:59,057
If you do, then I can promise you
a real future.

1038
00:58:59,683 --> 00:59:02,477
For both you and your grandmother.

1039
00:59:04,104 --> 00:59:05,272
A life of comfort.

1040
00:59:10,235 --> 00:59:11,194
<i>They do not</i>

1041
00:59:11,736 --> 00:59:13,488
<i>just share the same face.</i>

1042
00:59:14,114 --> 00:59:16,867
<i>They even share an affinity</i>
<i>for detestable antics.</i>

1043
00:59:18,618 --> 00:59:21,371
<i>Your Highness, I shall bring in the soup.</i>

1044
00:59:32,549 --> 00:59:33,717
Taste it for poison.

1045
00:59:49,858 --> 00:59:51,234
How does it taste?

1046
00:59:51,985 --> 00:59:53,028
It is a nourishing soup

1047
00:59:53,111 --> 00:59:55,739
made with the beast
I just caught in the rear garden.

1048
01:00:12,797 --> 01:00:15,091
Your Highness, I deserve death.

1049
01:00:15,675 --> 01:00:17,344
Killing you now would be a waste,

1050
01:00:17,969 --> 01:00:20,263
when you will be of great use to me.

1051
01:00:24,100 --> 01:00:27,229
I hear you are the court lady
who serves as a companion

1052
01:00:27,312 --> 01:00:29,814
to my brother with the damaged eye.

1053
01:00:38,448 --> 01:00:40,450
Become my brother's lover.

1054
01:00:41,910 --> 01:00:42,911
Or even…

1055
01:00:46,122 --> 01:00:47,499
his most cherished…

1056
01:00:49,501 --> 01:00:51,378
dog would suffice.

1057
01:01:09,813 --> 01:01:10,772
<i>Oh my gosh, Seo-ri!</i>

1058
01:01:10,855 --> 01:01:13,525
You're here.
Come here, my sweet girl.

1059
01:01:13,608 --> 01:01:15,402
You're really here.

1060
01:01:16,820 --> 01:01:18,488
<i>Have I ever, even once,</i>

1061
01:01:19,072 --> 01:01:22,200
<i>been loved unconditionally?</i>

1062
01:01:31,668 --> 01:01:33,003
<i>Ms. Shin.</i>

1063
01:01:33,086 --> 01:01:35,046
You should be friends with Cha Se-gye.

1064
01:01:35,130 --> 01:01:38,508
<i>Usefulness. Bait. Worth.</i>

1065
01:01:39,592 --> 01:01:41,219
<i>A life where none of that matters.</i>

1066
01:01:41,303 --> 01:01:42,470
<i>Where my existence</i>

1067
01:01:43,555 --> 01:01:45,307
<i>does not need to be justified.</i>

1068
01:02:10,957 --> 01:02:12,000
How wretched.

1069
01:02:14,002 --> 01:02:15,587
How can life be so…

1070
01:02:26,097 --> 01:02:29,351
This should be good enough
to bring a dog home.

1071
01:02:31,311 --> 01:02:33,355
SHRINE OF DOG

1072
01:02:47,952 --> 01:02:49,913
Why did I make this stupid thing?

1073
01:03:46,761 --> 01:03:47,887
Are you crying?

1074
01:04:29,721 --> 01:04:32,974
This is the best you could find
with the signing bonus I gave you?

1075
01:04:35,226 --> 01:04:36,728
Why a rooftop of all places?

1076
01:04:41,316 --> 01:04:43,568
What kind of building has no elevator?

1077
01:04:43,651 --> 01:04:45,320
And it's so dark.

1078
01:04:47,947 --> 01:04:49,282
Why are you here?

1079
01:04:51,242 --> 01:04:53,912
I see. You came to mock me
for believing wholeheartedly

1080
01:04:53,995 --> 01:04:55,955
that you were my fan, like a fool.

1081
01:05:04,255 --> 01:05:05,256
I'm sorry.

1082
01:05:13,765 --> 01:05:15,391
Your grandmother's restaurant…

1083
01:05:16,851 --> 01:05:18,436
I'll apologize on their behalf.

1084
01:05:20,230 --> 01:05:21,606
Don't worry too much.

1085
01:05:23,483 --> 01:05:24,776
No need.

1086
01:05:25,360 --> 01:05:27,779
From now on, I shall handle
my own business. Stay out of it.

1087
01:05:27,862 --> 01:05:29,405
How can I just stay out of it

1088
01:05:29,489 --> 01:05:31,658
when you're always lingering around?

1089
01:05:32,367 --> 01:05:35,828
Even now, you're sitting here looking
all forlorn but refusing to budge, so I…

1090
01:05:42,126 --> 01:05:43,294
-So I keep--
-You.

1091
01:05:44,170 --> 01:05:45,588
Do not look at me like that.

1092
01:05:47,382 --> 01:05:49,384
-Like what?
-With that look in your eyes.

1093
01:05:49,467 --> 01:05:50,927
With eyes full of pity.

1094
01:05:52,554 --> 01:05:54,180
Do not look at me with pity.

1095
01:05:55,306 --> 01:05:57,892
-How am I looking at you--
-When you look at me that way,

1096
01:05:57,976 --> 01:06:00,061
I keep drawing the wrong conclusion.

1097
01:06:00,144 --> 01:06:03,189
You are not my fan or on my side,
but you look at me like that.

1098
01:06:03,273 --> 01:06:04,566
It makes me think…

1099
01:06:07,110 --> 01:06:08,069
I am…

1100
01:06:13,950 --> 01:06:15,994
someone you harbor affection for.

1101
01:06:17,579 --> 01:06:19,122
-Affection?
-Yes. Affection.

1102
01:06:19,664 --> 01:06:23,126
Strangers do not worry about you
and cheer you on.

1103
01:06:23,209 --> 01:06:25,336
It is not just me.
Anyone would think that.

1104
01:06:26,588 --> 01:06:27,672
Stop it.

1105
01:06:44,480 --> 01:06:46,065
What if you weren't mistaken?

1106
01:06:49,652 --> 01:06:51,029
What?

1107
01:06:51,112 --> 01:06:53,031
I see strictly in black and white.

1108
01:06:53,448 --> 01:06:54,365
Black or white.

1109
01:06:54,449 --> 01:06:56,117
Ally or enemy. Love it or hate it.

1110
01:06:56,200 --> 01:06:57,493
But you're

1111
01:06:58,161 --> 01:06:59,454
neither one nor the other.

1112
01:07:01,873 --> 01:07:03,541
You keep confusing me.

1113
01:07:12,300 --> 01:07:13,384
Then let me enlighten you.

1114
01:07:38,534 --> 01:07:40,703
See? You remain unfazed.

1115
01:07:42,872 --> 01:07:44,999
That settles it, does it not?

1116
01:07:45,583 --> 01:07:46,793
No.

1117
01:07:47,377 --> 01:07:48,670
That won't suffice.

1118
01:07:50,588 --> 01:07:52,715
-If we're checking, we check thoroughly.
-How?

1119
01:07:52,799 --> 01:07:53,966
Like this.

1120
01:08:50,606 --> 01:08:54,152
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1121
01:09:24,256 --> 01:09:26,258
<i>A fierce war of courtship begins.</i>

1122
01:09:26,330 --> 01:09:28,430
It's a green light for me.
I've decided to pursue you.

1123
01:09:28,505 --> 01:09:30,646
<i>Once your heart wavers,</i>
<i>you become weak.</i>

1124
01:09:30,730 --> 01:09:33,316
<i>In this life, I shall become</i>
<i>a wealthy Buddhist nun.</i>

1125
01:09:33,399 --> 01:09:35,443
She's actually playing hard to get.

1126
01:09:35,526 --> 01:09:37,302
<i>Most males will shower</i>
<i>the females with gifts.</i>

1127
01:09:37,403 --> 01:09:38,971
<i>"I surrender! I'll die without you!"</i>

1128
01:09:39,071 --> 01:09:40,281
<i>Desperately…</i>

1129
01:09:40,364 --> 01:09:42,158
So stop being
so pathetically clingy. Jeez.

1130
01:09:42,909 --> 01:09:45,328
<i>-Don't say no a second time. Call me.</i>
-Have we met?

1131
01:09:45,411 --> 01:09:48,372
<i>In this courtship battle,</i>
<i>will he emerge victorious?</i>

1132
01:09:48,456 --> 01:09:50,833
<i>Do you truly harbor affection for me?</i>

1133
01:09:54,214 --> 01:09:56,214
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim

